abstract: >-
  An evidence-governed lifecycle for agentic software development, which we
  operationalize as Agentic Loop Engineering (ALE) — a term also used in prior
  agentic-SWE work (arXiv:2509.06216); our contribution is the integration, not
  the term. ALE maps the full software development life cycle onto a governable,
  auditable multi-agent pipeline. It studies a "shared-context false pass" — a
  correlated false-pass failure mode that may arise when the AI that verifies is
  also an AI sharing the producer's source or bias — and hypothesizes that
  multi-model cross-checking reduces variance but, under shared bias, may not
  remove systematic bias (a research hypothesis pending EXP-001). It proposes a
  three-layer verification architecture (mechanical gate / model panel / human
  review of evidence) and a Skill-Capitalization loop that turns each delivered
  project into a reusable, verifiable Skill. This is a working paper; core claims
  are labelled as research hypotheses pending EXP-001 / EXP-002 (no validated
  findings yet).
